The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 600) The legendary reunion of the Eagles, 

 the 70s cult band from southern California. One of the most 

 talked about acoustic concerts of all time is reproduced 

 in DTS quality here. Songs performed include Take It 

 Easy, Desperado, Love Will Keep Us Alive and, 

 of course, Hotel California.

 THE DISPLAY

 (Academy of Fine Arts, 2 pm-8 pm, till June 30) Rural artisans 

 of Bengal exhibit products of traditional crafts ? from 

 dokra, shola, woodcraft, and terracotta to hand-made 

 paper accessories, masks and grass mats. Presented by Nimble 

 Fingers. 

 THE SHOW

 (GD 

 Birla Sabhagar, 3.30 pm and 6.30 pm, June 26) Marathi poet 

 Arun Kolatkar is the protagonist of this play to be staged 

 by Chennai-based group Just Us, with verse, dialogues and 

 Carnatic music. Actor Dhritiman Chaterji enacts the poet in 

 myriad moods in the production for Odeon 2005. 




